You are working in repo cvsz/zeaz-platform.

Implement Phase 58 · cvsz apps merge/adoption system.

Goal:
Deep-dive apps/ABTPi18n and apps/zkbtrader, then create safe scripts to adopt all apps/* that correspond to cvsz/* repos into zeaz-platform.

Rules:
- zeaz-platform remains the operator monorepo.
- apps/zdash is already integrated and must not be broken.
- apps/zeaz-api and apps/zeaz-web are internal root apps, not cvsz imports by default.
- apps/ABTPi18n and apps/zkbtrader are P1 deep-dive targets.
- Remove nested .git only with explicit APPLY=true and CONFIRM_CVSZ_APPS_MERGE=yes.
- Before removing nested .git, write apps/<app>/IMPORT_SOURCE.md with origin, branch, and HEAD.
- Do not commit .env, .env.production, .env.cloudflare, tfstate, tfvars, tfplan, node_modules, .venv, build artifacts, caches, token logs, sqlite/db files.
- Do not run live trading, social posting, external automation, Cloudflare mutation, Terraform apply, token rotation, or deployment.
- No auto commit. Scripts must stop after preparing files.

Deliverables:
- configs/repos/cvsz-apps-merge-map.json
- scripts/apps/deep-dive-critical-apps.sh
- scripts/apps/plan-cvsz-apps-merge.py
- scripts/apps/adopt-cvsz-apps-apply.sh
- scripts/apps/validate-cvsz-apps-merge.sh
- docs/runbooks/CVSZ_APPS_MERGE_ADOPTION.md
- Makefile targets:
  - critical-apps-deep-dive
  - cvsz-apps-merge-plan
  - cvsz-apps-merge-apply
  - cvsz-apps-merge-validate
  - phase58-validate

Acceptance:
- make critical-apps-deep-dive works
- make cvsz-apps-merge-plan works
- make cvsz-apps-merge-validate clearly reports blockers
- apply target is guarded
- no secrets or generated reports are staged
- git diff --check passes
